  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">HIV+ Survivors Integration Project (SIP)</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The survivors of the genocide in Rwanda continue to be the most vulnerable and isolated community in the country, and many of the women are stigmatised from being raped and living with HIV. Many widows are struggling to make ends meet, to reclaim their property, rebuild their houses and raise their children. The Survivors Fund supports survivors living with HIV to access health care and provides social support to meet their basic needs. This includes specialised counselling, home-based care, legal aid and opportunities to earn a living. Children orphaned through the genocide, or born as a result of rape, are supported to attend school and complete their studies. In addition to supporting survivors with their day-to-day needs, the project is lobbying government and international donors for long-term support for survivors.</narrative>
  </description>
